Luke Carrick was unexpectedly "press-ganged" into Royal Navy service at the height of the Napoleonic Wars in the early 19th Century. Serving on board the HMS Hera, a frigate, Luke's resentment at his treatment and loathing of authority steadily grew as the ship embarked on a series of increasingly dangerous voyages.

Luke's older brother, Silas, had died in mysterious circumstances a few years earlier. Convinced that the British officer responsible for Silas' death was now fighting alongside him, vengeance - even more than survival - was now on the young sailor's mind.

Introduction

With only a few notable exceptions - step forward the Convict Commandos - recurring characters have been rare on the pages of Commando over the last 50-odd years. However we were of the opinion that you, our readers, might like a series which carried the story over more than one issue. With the pen of Ferg Handley recruited to do the writing, we decided that a historical saga spanning many generations would hit the spot.

Episode Nine sees the continuing story of three - entirely fictional -inter-linked families and how they find themselves in the thick of the action of the Napoleonic Wars.

The majority of this exciting instalment takes place at sea - with Royal Navy vessels clashing against their French counterparts. Yet for one of our characters, these tumultuous battles are only a backdrop to a personal quest for revenge…

We hope you enjoy this story and the journey to come.

Scott Montgomery, Deputy Editor
name: Voyage of the Eagles

description:
Purple with rage, the Luftwaffe squadron leader shook his fist at the lone Typhoon disappearing over the horizon. All around him, shattered planes and burning hangars covered his blitzed airfield, victims of one pilot.

And on the airfield in Belgium a British squadron leader scanned the horizon for the same plane. He was furious too. That plane was his own brand-new Typhoon, and it had been stolen!

Introduction

This is classic Commando in every sense. From the wonderfully lurid colours of Ken Barr's cover, to Gordon Livingstone's dynamic black-and-white line art and McOwan (first name unknown)'s all-important script - these three elements fuse together perfectly for an epic tale of guts versus glory.

When a plucky mechanic takes it upon himself to stand up to a ruthless squadron leader, we're set for a brilliant story which is all about one man having the courage to do the right thing, whatever the cost.

Scott Montgomery, Deputy Editor

Note: Originally published as Commando No 312 (February 1968) and re-issued as No 1027 (May 1976).
name: Rocket Blitz

description:
Salerno, Italy, 1943.

Life as a sniper suited Lance-Corporal Eric Shaw. He had seen a lot of mates die after a couple of tragic accidents and now he had become a loner - guilty that he had survived when they hadn't.

His sharp-shooting skills improved with each day and he tried to help out any Allied troops whenever he could. Nonetheless, Eric was unexpectedly working alongside a fellow sharp-shooter - an American. Little did the two crack-shots know that soon the hunters would became the hunted - in the SNIPER ZONE
name: Sniper Zone

description:
They were trapped in neutral Spain - the pilot of a ditched Hurricane and the first mate of a merchant ship which had also become a casualty of war.

They weren't the best of mates, but they were all that stood between the British fleet at Gibraltar and a lethal strike force. The odds were stacked against them, but they weren't quitters, and now was the time to take DESPERATE MEASURES

Introduction

As ever, veteran Commando artist Ian Kennedy's terrific cover gives us a tantalising glimpse of what this book is all about.

Air and sea - as a Fleet Air Arm Hurricane blasts from a cam-ship via catapult…we see that there is also some kind of mysterious raid happening underneath the murky depths of the ocean, led by a pair of manned torpedo chariots.

Air and sea - as a pilot and a sailor bitterly clash.

Air and sea - with both combining to form a winning Commando story.

Scott Montgomery, Deputy Editor

Note: Originally published as Commando No 2698 (September 1993).
name: Desperate Measures

description: The TARDIS has recently been on the fritz, but now it has gone completely out of control. And the Doctor is nowhere to be found! Meanwhile, white holes have been forming throughout time and space, sucking in everything around them. What does the Hypothetical Gentleman have to do with it all? Find out in the four-part story 'Sky Jacks'!
name: Sky Jacks Part 1

volume.name: Doctor Who: The Eleventh Doctor Archives

description: The missing TARDIS has been found! But now the TARDIS has vanished, leaving him and his companion stranded in a strange dimension with seemingly infinite skies! How do they plan to escape this steampunk world? By using a World War II-era atomic bomb, of course!
name: Sky Jacks Part 2

volume.name: Doctor Who: The Eleventh Doctor Archives

description: The nature of the 'sky world' has been revealed! But the mystery of how it cam into being still eludes the Doctor. But with Clara and the crew of a retrofitted B-29 bomber from World War II in tow, the Doctor sets out for the center of this strange dimension with seemingly infinite skies!
name: Sky Jacks Part 3

volume.name: Doctor Who: The Eleventh Doctor Archives

description: The big bad revealed at last! The mystery of the Hypothetical Gentelman and his identity has finally been unraveled by the Doctor, but is it too late to save himself, Clara and the other misplaced residents of 'sky world'?
name: Sky Jacks Part 4

volume.name: Doctor Who: The Eleventh Doctor Archives

description: Earth Invasion: Performance Issues Grzzt foils a capture attempt by rouge military elements. Meanwhile, the aliens devastate Athens, Greece. Martha Cortez' past is revealed and a 'little party' is held at Nate's place with Pepe and some hired help. In the morning, they are watching Reverend Sean Sullivan's broadcast, which we follow and find out something shocking about him!
name: Performance Issues

description: Earth Invasion: The Sean Sullivan Show The pasts of Maria Berenyi and Sean Sullivan are revealed. Maria rises from being violently orphaned to exchange student to Ivy League standout. Sean comes from a long line of con artists and is the family black sheep until he 'discovers' his signature scam. His full indulgence of the perks get him in trouble though!
name: The Sean Sullivan Show

description: Earth Invasion: Second Act More of the pasts of several characters is revealed. Meanwhile, Pepe Macias, Pamela Greenberg, Willy, & Cleopatra are sent on a dangerous mission!
name: Second Act

description: Earth Invasion: The Princess and the Pauper Pamela Greenberg and Pepe Macias are captured by a plunder gang, but Willy and Cleopatra escape -- can they get help for their captive humans? Meanwhile, Maria Berenyi meets her supervisor...and it is someone with whom she has a history!
name: The Princess and the Pauper

description: Earth Invasion: Coercion While in captivity, Pamela Greenberg shares some of her past with Pepe Macias. Meanwhile, the rest of the team assembles to rescue their fellows, and do so with the help of some new gadgetry from Grzzt.
name: Coercion

description:
Former crime fighting sidekick Jason Bronze wakes up to a world that has long forgotten the caped heroes that once protected it. Not having aged a day and his own memories scattered, he must discover what has happened over the last forty years. But he'll soon find that he wasn't the only one who has returned. The worst criminals, the Serials--influenced by the 'green glow', a mysterious substance used as both a power source and a narcotic, have also resurfaced to wreak havoc on an unsuspecting Justice City. Can Jason overcome the decades long absence to assume the mantle of his former mentor, THE GREEN OWL? Or will he succumb to the most dangerous threat he faces--his own inner demons?

OsbournDraw presents an all-new, expanding universe of masked heroes, super-powered vigilantes and criminal masterminds in a series of comic books and graphic novels that celebrate the past, present and future ages of comics while forging its own path of creativity, diversity, and original storytelling.

As former sidekick Jason Bronze struggles to find his place in the present day, he comes face to face with his childhood friend Max Mason and the villainous, immortal known only as Cyrano. Can the fractured memories of the past guide his future? And who or what is waiting in the shadows to propel Jason towards his ultimate destiny as this generation's Emerald Enforcer, The Green Owl!

The mob families of Justice City, feeling cut out of the criminal underworld by the Serials, the supervillains who have recently awoken from a 40 year slumber, seek an alliance with the mysterious End of the World Gang, a cult group with apocalyptic desires. Meanwhile, fully under the Spore's control, Colin returns to Team Owl, who are oblivious to the enemy that has infiltrated their ranks. And as machinations transpire from afar, the evil mastermind Cyrano rises…

Plus, this issue features a guest appearance by Soldier Spook!

It's back to school for Green Owl and Harrowing! There's definitely something awry in the halls of this institution of higher learning--but is it the students, the faculty, or something else? After all, this is Superville Academy, the sister building of the old asylum and something just as dangerous is brewing below the foundation. As the heroes go undercover to find the truth, Green Owl will come face to face with his forgotten past--and Harrowing--he may just get detention--the kind you don't get out of alive!

For the first time in years, former sidekick and current Green Owl Jason Bronze is not alone--he's reconnected with Nick, his old mentor, and Astra, another of the old super team, The Power Society. While old friends emerge, so do old enemies--the Serials--supervillains from forty years ago who, along with Jason, escaped their cryogenic slumber.

New ally Mags Reilly joins Harrowing on patrol and faces the strangest villain yet--Pamela Purz, a former scientist who's partner emerges from her handbag as a hulking, glow-infected beast. Meanwhile, reporter Katie Doyle is still suspicious of the new Superville Academy chancellor and soon finds herself in a dangerous situation--one that only Astra the Galactic Girl can save them from! But the former hero has a secret--one that may doom everyone in Justice City!

There's a storm brewing in Justice City! Cyrano's plan to punish the world is on the cusp of being unleashed as Cyrano himself struggles to piece together the fragmented memories of his past. But the missing pieces are slowly coming back to him as he recalls the shocking moment that turned him from two-bit criminal to the world's most sinister supervillain.

Meanwhile, Nick Terrance, the long-retired crimefighter, and Harrowing investigate a series of mobsters murdered in a way that recalls the methods of another former golden-aged hero. And Green Owl continues training Dorian as a sidekick, but the younger hero's increasingly violent outbursts mask a major flashpoint in his past that led him to track down the Green Owl!

And then, an army rises…

As a former sidekick and now as the bearer of the cowl, Green Owl Jason Bronze has had one imperative--to protect Justice City from those that would harm it. Now, that mission is crumbling as the vengeance-filled master criminal Cyrano and his army of followers pour into the streets, terrorizing the citizenry and easily decimating the police force. Too strong for Team Owl, the heroes retreat to the Owl cave in defeat. But Cyrano is about to do what no other villain dared--take the battle into the stronghold of the heroes! Watch out Green Owl, Cyrano is coming… and before the sun rises one of the heroes will fall!

CONCLUSION! It's all comes down to this! The villain Cyrano has breached the Owl cave and struck Green Owl and his team of young heroes by killing their trusted friend and advisor. But Cyrano's ultimate plan is even more sinister as he seeks to control the alien technology below Justice City and use it to destroy the Earth! Can Green Owl save the day once more--or will he have to make the ultimate sacrifice? The final pages of this book will change the Owlverse forever!

description:
Inside this issue: A patient seeks psychiatric counselling when his dreams of distant planets begin to physically affect him, zombies cause bedlam at the local zoo, a man of medicine in ancient Egypt begins to raise heretical questions about his profession, an overly dedicated postman crosses a post apocalyptic wasteland in an attempt to make a first class delivery, a psychologically disturbed individual begins to lose his grip on reality after dying over a hundred times in his sleep, one lone soul crosses the treacherous plains of Yomi, and Travis Wilson attempts to drown his sorrows at a Martian casino in the third instalment of Death Duty (all other strips are self contained).

Featuring the likes of John Freeman (Marvel UK, Judge Dredd Megazine), Gary Crutchley (2000ad, WESTERnoir), Mats Engesten (Final Death Race, Autopsy), Paul Harrison-Davies (Boom Studios, Blank Slate), Tony Suleri (Slumdroid, Cosmogenesis) and many more!

This issue also features a hand painted cover by the ever-talented Alan Burrows (2000ad, Transmetropolitan: Tales Of Human Waste, and co-creator of Death Duty)

By Dan Slott, Olivier Coipel, Humberto Ramos, Christos Gage, David Williams and more!

description: Issue 2 continues BSaTT's commitment to telling a variety of different stories with some of today's hottest up and coming talent. However, whereas Issue 1 exclusively told self-contained stories, Issue 2 has three brand new stories that each end "To be continued ..." You, the readers, have the ability to vote on our Facebook page and decide which one of the three stories will first be continued in its own solo issue!

Book Two

In Book Two of Ellen Lindner's murder mystery series, a woolly clue takes our hero­ine and her prickly companion to the remotest part of Scotland - but is it all a wild goose chase?
name: Book Two

description: The 'Throne of God' killer is dead, but Detective Drekker can’t shake the feeling that the killings are not. In the maddened eyes of the killer Drekker is reminded of an old case. We continue to explore that case through the eyes of one of its survivors, Edmund. Somehow it is connected to The Throne, and Drekker is determined to unlock its mysteries. The children have begun to band together for support and protection against The Boogeyman Killer; Christian offers up a horrifying explanation; and the moment of Zero draws closer. Boy Zero is an epic noir spanning decades and two separate murder mysteries. The cases are somehow connected and Detective Drekker must connect them before the killings begin again.

The Bravest Warriors have crashed! Shot down by a mysterious enemy, the gang is stranded on an uncharted planet with no way off or help in sight. While the rest of the team tries to find a way to survive (and pass the time), Chris struggles to accept his Emotion Lord abilities and begins to doubt whether or not he should even be a Bravest Warrior. Written by the showrunners of Bravest Warriors, Jason Johnson & Breehn Burns, and illustrated by Mike Holmes (True Story), this volume takes place during season 2 of the hit animated series. Collects issues #17-#20.

Note: The digital edition (8/13/2015) for this volume was released before the print edition.
name: Volume Five

description: Kevin Nivek, head of the Secret Service and in charge of security for the President of the United States, is fired after an assassination attempt almost succeeds. While investigating what he believes is a conspiracy among the various American intelligence services, he meets Debrah, a mysterious and formidable young woman who works for a secret organization. He learns that for centuries, and from deep in the shadows, the Stryx have influenced human destiny.
name: Shadows 2/2

description:
Underground Operation

A mutated cybernetic boar searches for his place in the world. Looking for peace, Cy-boar usually finds only danger, and skull splitting action!

CY-BOAR #10: UNDERGROUND OPERATION

After narrowly escaping a brainwashing set-up that made him an assassin, Cy-Boar wants answers! With the aid of Kayla and Squirrel, what top secret operation will Cy uncover?
name: Underground Operation

description:
On the Run

Crimson and Caress of the Cyberines have had enough and they are On the Run from the only family they've ever known.
name: On the Run
